pageContext.claim: “John James, he's a star. He's going to be a star and you have somebody that's very special, And, uh, you know, his competition, nobody knows who the hell he is. Peters.”
pageContext.analysis: This is nonsense. Republican John James ran against Michigan’s incumbent senator, Gary Peters. Peters was first elected to the Senate in 2014 after serving as a member of the U.S. House of Representatives.
